Here is the root cause:
The bug was caused by the lack of restrictions on file writing paths, allowing files to be written outside the designated starting directory, which could lead to security vulnerabilities and unintended file system access. The new feature aims to enforce a default behavior that restricts file writing to the starting directory and its subdirectories, enhancing security.

